<br>
Just a tip.<br>
<br>
Spread out your pets.  If you cast your HotE ability and have all your pets fighting from the same drop point your little pets are going to push that mob around which you may not want to have happen.<br>
<br>
The push may not be a big problem in open areas but in caves and tight areas it can easily push your target into other mobs, off ledges or up walls.<br>
<br>
What I do is I start at one side of the mob and strafe around the mob leaving a nice rainbow around the mobs back half.  It's reduces the directional push and allows your groupmates to see how many freaken pets you have.<br>
<br>
Although against casting mobs it may be beneficial to group up your pets to move the target around so that the casting is interrupted. <p><a target="Amel Rathanon" href="http://www.familjenguild.com/dspMember.php?Name=Amel">Sage Amel Rathanon {Arch Convoker}</a><br>
